******************************************************************************
CREATING A NEW CHEMISTRY MECHANISM:
******************************************************************************

1) The directory mecca/kpp/bin already contains the KPP executable for
   32-bit linux. If this cannot be used, install "flex" and compile KPP
   with:

   cd mecca/kpp
   make

2) Start the script xmecca and give the name of a suitable batch file,
   e.g.:

   ./xmecca simple

   For details, see CAABA/MECCA manual.

******************************************************************************
INSTALLING AND RUNNING THE MODEL:
******************************************************************************

1) Install the Fortran 90 compiler "g95". Alternatively, if you want to
   use a different compiler, edit "Makefile" and enter your compiler
   settings there.

2) Compile the code by running "make".

3) Start the executable "mecca.exe".

******************************************************************************

******************************************************************************
WARNING
******************************************************************************
This simple MESSy Base Model (MBM) mecca can only deal with simple
gas phase mechanisms. Het and Aq reactions are not supported.
